                     Ezechiah finding God fauourable to him in this free pardon of his ſinnes, doth confeſſe it, and hee expreſſeth it thus;
Thou haſt caſt all my ſinnes behinde thy back.
                           Iſ. 38.17.

Obiect. 1 That Chriſt hath ſatisfied his father for the ſinnes of all the elect, for ſo ſaith Iſaiah;
Iſ. 53.5. He was wounded for our tranſgreſsion, he was bruiſed for our iniquities, the chaſtiſement of our peace was vpon him, and with his ſtripes are we healed.
6. And God laid on him the iniquity of vs all.

Who ſo offereth praiſe, glorifieth me;
Pſal. 50.23. 
Dauid often calleth it Sacrificium laudis. And he calleth theſe kinde of ſacrifices, the ſacrifices of righteouſneſſe.
